dford capital corporation from march  to march  and vice president of bedford from september  to march  prior to cofounding bedford he served as vice president and director of mergers  acquisitions of merrill lynch inc where he specialized in management buyouts and divestitures mr beattie served as also a manager of andersen consulting specializing in the design and implementation of enterprise resource planning systems since the inception of ffi in  he has been actively involved in ffis management and development including the recruitment of members of senior management brand acquisitions and financings business strategy development and implementation customer and supplier relationships and other operating activities mr beattie served as chairman of elizabeth arden inc since april  he has been nonexecutive vicechairman of revlon inc since september   he has been director of elizabeth arden inc since january  he serves as director of bedford capital corporation and bcc advisors inc he serves as director of the cosmetic toiletry  fragrance association and a member of the advisory board of the ivey business school he also serves as a director of the fragrance foundation inc he served as a director of objectvideo inc since december   mr beattie earned a master of business administration in  and a bachelor of arts degree in honors business administration in  both from the university of western ontario ivey school of businessread full background corporate headquarters  sw  avenuespembroke pines florida united statesphone fax  board members memberships presentchairman chief executive officer and presidentelizabeth arden incpresentnonexecutive vicechairmanrevlon inc education ba university of western ontario ivey school of businessmba university of western ontario ivey school of business other affiliations bedford capital management increvlon incobjectvideo incuniversity of western ontario ivey school of business annual compensation salarytotal annual compensation stocks o