 equity firm he cofounded in  prior to that he served as a vice president in the mergers and acquisitions group of merrill lynch inc and as a manager of accenture consulting mr beattie earned a masters degree in business administration in  and a bachelor of arts degree in honors business administration in  both from the ivey business school at western university he currently serves on the board and executive committee of the personal care products council the board of directors of pencil object video inc and the ivey business school mr beattie has made philanthropy fundamental to the culture of elizabeth arden the company supports a wide range of charitable humanitarian and educational causes including look good… feel better the world heart federations go red for women campaign make a wish foundation pencil public education needs civic involvement in learning in nyc public schools the fashion institute of technology save the children and other endeavours previous next return to membership ivey business school  western road london ontario canada ng n our campuses » contact us » careers » programs hba mba msc executive mba executive education phd hong kong code of conduct directories faculty research case sales deans office news  publications intouch news and events impact ivey business journal ivey purchasing managers index ivey publishing resources ezone alumni portal web outlook cb bud johnston library my ivey  ivey business school     terms of use    privacy policy    western university scott beattie  giving to western log in user name password why log innew usertrouble signing in westernuca western alumni foundation western menu the campaign where to give ways to give your impact donate the campaign priority areas leadership progress extraordinary alumni news  announcements where to give ways to give monthly  onetime gifts endowed gifts bequests  planned gifts memorial  honour gifts international gifts your impact recognition donor profiles publications appreciation notes success stories donate home  the campaign  extraordinary alumni scott beattie hba’ mba’ is one of the most respected names in the beauty products industry as chairman and ceo of elizabeth arden inc he has transformed the company into a global powerhouse through his vision and leadership in product innovation and brand development and he developed his business acumen at western biography how does someone go from cofounding a private equity firm to leading a global cosmetics companye scott beattie hba’ mba’ hears that question a lot through his career beattie has moved from being an investment banker to leading an international beauty brand – elizabeth arden inc he responds to the question by saying his business knowledge plus his openness to new opportunities made the transition a logical fit he encourages the next generation of leaders to do the same“don’t try to manage your career let the opportunities blossom as they occur” beattie said at an event for western students at ivey business school “listen to your heart” he has followed his own advice after earning two degrees from ivey beattie set out on his business career he began with andersen consulting now accenture and then switched to mergers and acquisitions with merrill lynch in  he cofounded bedford capital a torontobased private equity firm involved in financing managing and developing businesses in the consumer product financial services it and retail sectors  now as chairman president and ceo of elizabeth arden beattie has been involved in every element of the company’s global expansion and modern transformation since its inception in  through his focus on product innovation and brand development beattie has grown the company into one of the world’s most recognizable beauty brands with more than  billion in revenue and a presence in  countrieswith all of his success beattie finds time to stayed involved with western serving on the ivey advisory board and returning to campus to share leadership lessons with students during one session with ivey students he encouraged them to boldly pursue their interests always keep learning and lead with integrity and humility “when you look at companies that fail it’s not often because of lack of competence but because of arrogance” beattie told students “when you get in front of people you have to behave with the highest level of integrity people are always looking at you as a leader you need to lead by example” extraordinary alumni vandana shiva tomson highway stephen poloz stephan moccio stacey allaster shelley ambrose scott russell sarah richardson roberta jamieson randy lai perrin beatty paul beeston michael hyatt marnie mcbean marilyn emery marie wilson louise pitre linda hasenfratz ken chu joseph rotman jordan banks janet bannister jack cowin harley pasternak glenn stevens george cope dr peter armstrong dr margaret chan david patchellevans david mckay dale ponder catherine karakatsanis cameron bailey bonnie schmidt bob blumer featured initiative iveys new home more information on the ivey business schools campaign priorities contact us eric graage executive director advancement ivey business school  abbey baran associate director corporate relations ivey business school     western universitywestern university department of alumni relations  development westminster hall suite  london ontario canada na k tel  or  toll free givinguwoca privacy  web guidelines  terms of use  accessibilitycharitable business number   rr the campaignwhere to giveways to giveyour impactdonatebe involved western alumnifoundation westernalumni gazette nonprofit software why log in logging into the giving to western web site at wwwgivingwesternuca allows you to update your personal information manage the types of email you receive from western easily register for events with prepopulated forms use the western alumni online directory once your alumni status is confirmed what about my privacy western treats all personal information in confiden